{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Allow employees to deduct living expenses from salary before it\u2019s taxed.",
        "additional_details": "I believe this change could bring about several key benefits 1) Increase in disposable income. 2) Reduction in financial stress 3) Fairer taxation system. I believe that the tax system has loopholes for the rich and some large companies do not pay a fair amount of tax. I also think that a large percentage of tax is wasted, and it is therefore only fair to let people keep more of their income, and funding this could include reducing public services.  ",
        "background": "I\u2019d like to propose that the Government allow employees to deduct essential living expenses\u2014such as rent/mortgage, utility bills, food, council tax and childcare\u2014from their income before it is subject to tax. ",
